result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael Lee Alloway Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
The defendant must maintain/obtain full time employment/school that consists of at least 35 hrs/week.

When not full time employed/school, the defendant must apply for at least 3 jobs per week and report progress monthly to P&P with pertinent information in regards to applications.  The defendant must only apply for jobs qualified for - must accept any job offered - must not engage in any conduct that could result in the termination of his/her employment/school.

Must obtain GED within first year of probation.

No possession/consumption of alcohol.

No entry into any bars/taverns.
Right to expunge under 973.015 upon successful completion of probation.
The defendant must undergo an AODA assessment and follow thru with all recommendations.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Michael Lee Alloway in court with attorney Paul Arbuckle.  Defendant Michael Lee Alloway in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 11:30 PM. Also called 15CM32. State - updates Court on the matters but both matters are resolved. State - has complied with victim notification requirements with no response - amend count #1 on 15CM32 to county ordinance of DC with a forfeiture of $300 plus costs, remaining counts will be dismissed. Arbuckle - on 15CF172 - G to count #2 as alleged - 30 days jail, G on Counts #3 and #4 as alleged - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years with $300 fine plus costs on each count with standard probation conditions, dismiss and read in remaining counts. State agrees with agreement as stated by Arbuckle. Alloway agrees. Court - 15CM32 - dismisses counts #2, #3 and #4, amends count #1 to county ordinance of DC. Alloway pleads NC to amended count #1. Court finds guilty, sentences to a forfeiture of $300.00 plus costs totalling $582.50 - 60 DTP/CO including previous jury fees that were assessed. Court - 15CF172 - court dismisses and reads in counts #1, #5 and #6. Alloway pleads NC to counts #2, #3 and #4 as alleged. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation - 17 days credit on jail time. Arbuckle makes final argument prior to sentencing - follow joint recommendation. Alloway withholds comment. State would like to add a condition of probation that he have no contact with Tia Gilligan for stated reasons. Alloway and Arbuckle have no objections to that condition being added. Court sentences the defendant to the following: count #2 - 30 days in FC jail - huber and good time allowed - eligible for community service under 973.03(3) - credit for 17 days, costs only - 60 DTP/CO, on counts #3 and #4 - withhold sentence and place on probation for 2 years - concurrent to each other, with conditions of: AODA and follow thru, no possession or consumption of alcohol and no entry into any bars or taverns, $300.00 fine on each count plus surcharges including DNA surcharge - paid thru probation, employment/school, obtain GED within first year of probation, submit DNA sample, right to appeal, right to expunge under 973.015. Bond forfeiture - sets aside forfeiture on 15CF172 - use for fines.
No contact with victim (MLA - DOB 1/27/99), maintain absolute sobriety, no consumption or possession of alcohol or illegal drugs

Defendant Michael Lee Alloway in court, in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 12:03 PM. State - the defendant has been apprehended on a warrant from 15CM32. Court reads charges and penalties. Alloway wants attorney. State - bond - $5000 cash for stated reasons. Alloway withholds comment. Court - bond - $5000.00 cash, standard bond conditions, no contact with victim (MLA - DOB 1/27/99), maintain absolute sobriety, no consumption or possession of alcohol or illegal drugs, sets for AIA, instructed to contact SPD by end of this week.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for November 18, 2015 at 10:30 am.
Bonded out prior to probable cause.
